President Obama has appointed Jeffrey S. Crowley, a leading public health policy expert, as the Director of the Office of National AIDS Policy. Crowley will coordinate the government's efforts on HIV/AIDS policy and help develop disability policies. The Office of National AIDS Policy focuses on reducing HIV infections in the US through prevention and coordinating care and treatment for those with HIV/AIDS. Crowley is recognized for his ability to integrate public health research with political strategy and has expertise in Medicaid and Medicare policy. He previously worked at the National Association of People with AIDS and has spent years improving access to health and social services for vulnerable populations. Crowley holds a Master of Public Health from Johns Hopkins University and a Bachelor of Arts in Chemistry from Kalamazoo College. He is also an alumnus of the United States Peace Corps.